      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway-client): unref WS socket in beginStop() to fix CLI hang (#88230)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`openclaw message send` hangs after successful delivery because the gateway client's WebSocket socket stays ref'd in the Node event loop. `beginStop()` calls `ws.close()` and starts the close handshake, but the underlying `_socket` file descriptor remains ref'd, so Node's event loop never drains to zero active handles and a natural process exit never happens.\n\nThis adds a single `.unref()` call on `ws._socket` immediately after `ws.close()` inside `beginStop()`, wrapped in try/catch because `_socket` is an internal property of the `ws` package with no public contract.\n\nCloses #88230.\n\n## Why a new PR (supersedes #88282)\n\nPR #88282 targeted the old `src/gateway/client.ts` location. After the package refactor that moved `GatewayClient` into `packages/gateway-client/`, the PR went dirty/conflicting against main and was flagged `needs-real-behavior-proof`. This is the same one-line behavioral fix, rebased onto the new location, with a smaller targeted test that lives next to the implementation. I'll close #88282 once this is in your review queue.\n\n## Verification\n\n- New file: `packages/gateway-client/src/client.socket-unref.test.ts`\n  - `unrefs the underlying socket on stop() so the event loop can drain` — pins the behavioral fix\n  - `tolerates a ws without an internal _socket (defensive contract)` — confirms the try/catch path\n  - Same ws-injection pattern as the existing `client.watchdog.test.ts`\n- `vitest run packages/gateway-client/` — **50/50 pass** locally (12 watchdog + 10 timeouts + 1 event-loop-ready + 2 new socket-unref + workspace duplicates)\n\n## Why this is safe\n\n- `stopAndWait()` semantics unchanged — still resolves via the close event or force-terminate fallback\n- `forceTerminateTimer.unref()` was already in place; this matches its pattern\n- Try/catch ensures forward-compatibility if `ws` ever removes `_socket`\n- Public TypeScript types not touched\n\n🪶",
        "branch": "fix/88230-gateway-client-socket-unref-v2",
        "head_sha": "77fdc78c4a5abe3a2af544abb80c249ef81d56e1",
